Mar 26 2009 	Don't stay at The Pearl Residence unless you are desperate!	I stayed at Pearl Residence on a 2 day stop-over en route to New Zealand and then another 2 days on the way back to South Africa.First of all, in South African terms, this hotel is pricey. At around R1 500 per night, the same money would get you a top hotel in SA. In Dubai, this hotel is no frills, ugly and the staff really couldn't care less.From the outside, Pearl Residence looks quite nice with it's slick mirrored windows. That's about as good as it gets. The hotel is situated in the Burj area which is the older part of Dubai and about 5 minutes walk from Burjuman shopping mall which has a lovely selection of shops.My first room was situated on the first floor. The room had a basic kitchenette with a fridge, microwave, stove (which didn't work) and some basic cutlery and crockery. There was no kettle so not being able to make tea/coffee was a bit of a downer. The decor was stuck in the 80's and pretty ugly. The beds were hard and the linen threadbare. The small TV worked but only had 4 channels - of which 2 were English.I'd advise you to bring along your own bath towel as the bathroom had only a hand towel. On the plus side, the room was clean and had a working iron and ironing board.The breakfast buffet served every morning is pretty much the same every day. There is a small selection of items including cold cereals, juices, breads, cooked eggs, sausage, noodles with peas and a curried dish.The second room I stayed in was on the 5th floor. My travel agent had arranged an early check-in for me, but this time I had to wait 3 hours in the lobby for the room to be ready. After a 22 hour flight, this was not exactly a pleasant experience. There was a strong and constant gas odour as many other reviewers have noted. This room seemed a little more updated decor-wise but still 80's style with the same threadbare linen on a hard bed. I didn't test the stove out this time.There was a sparkling pool on the roof which I discovered on my second stay, as well as a small gym. I didn't test out either.The reception staff are absolutely not interested in helping out / giving advice. They wouldn't even call me a taxi! Don't even bother with them. They seemed anxious and irritated when ever I approached them. All in all, not a pleasant stay in a very basic hotel. Only stay here if you have no where else to go. You have been warned!	
