May 15 2008 	Don't be fooled by its looks	The hotel looks good from the outside but the interior has much to be desired. Rooms are spacious but depressing. Bathrooms leaked. The location is good as there is a shopping mall just behind the hotel. Also, the night market during the shopping festival is walking distance. Although, if you want to go to the Mall of the emirates or Jumeirah beach, it is a distance.If you do decide on this hotel, it is difficult to find a taxi on the road. Rather go to the mall and get a taxi from there.Avoid traffic between 4 and 6pm.	
Apr 1 2008 	Basic Tacky Only for Business!	My husband and i, and our 15yr old daughter stayed in Pearl Residence on a stopover. The hotel is located in an average area, that I would not recommend for holidays. The foyer was tacky and the furnishings in general were very average. The room we stayed in had a bedroom with ensuite, seperate living area and kitchenette and seperate toilet. The walls were painted an awful pastel green and the couch and chairs in the living room were very basic. The bed my daughter slept on in the bedroom was fine but the sheets were threadbare and barely fit the bed! There were visible stains, and the room did not feel properly cleaned at all. The staff were very friendly and helpful though, and spoke english very well. The porters took our bags with no complaint up the front entrance stairs as we got out of the taxi. The receptionist was very helpful and friendly and organized a dhow dinner cruise for us that night.I would only recommend this hotel if you are staying in Dubai on business or on a stopover (and you only want to sleep!), and are looking to save money. The hotel is near empty construction lots and a taxi is needed to get to the tourists spots. I would not recommend staying in Bur Dubai area or Deira for those on holiday. However it was reasonably close to the airport.	
