Nov 16 2005	Good servicequietclean rooms.	We stayed two days at Pearl Residences on our way from Australia to Europe and on return. As we arrived at 5am in the morning and departed at 2:30am in the morning we appreciated the 24 hour check-in/check out facility. No waiting for a room when all you want is a shower and some sleep after a long flight.Room was clean,spacious and simply furnished, consisting of bedroom, sitting area and well equiped kitchen nook with refrigerator,cook-top and microwave. Bathroom was plain but clean with shower over bath.Good supply of towels. Washing machine and dryer in the building basement.Our room was on the fourth floor at the side and was very quiet. No noisy nightclub downstairs which is a plus. The buffet breakfast is excellent with a good choice of hot and cold dishes.Reception area is plain and simple and staff spoke good english and were helpful. Location is a bit of a walk from the Creek in hot weather but taxis are cheap and plentiful. Just a short walk to the huge Bur Juman shopping center. Resturants nearby on Khalid bin al-Waleed Rd.Quiet, clean and good value.	
